<br>
But the two things I don't understand are: Why do mages <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> need</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a pet upgrade?  The only place I haven't been in the game is Sleeper's Tomb (Sleeper is awake on Vaz, no real need for me to go there till the revamp if that's not live yet) and Vex Thal (My guild is workin on their Emp strat...be a matter of time).  I'll be damned if the Epic isn't enough for every zone I've been in.  Granted, PoP is gonna be a whole different ballgame, and I expect more difficult mobs.  But of all the speculation about PoP, anything that says &quot;We'll <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> need</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> stronger pets because the mobs in PoP are tougher&quot; is flat unfounded...unless you are a beta tester.  Then again, if you read their post about the level cap, they say they are trying to make encounters more a test of strategy and such, not so much hours upon hours of &quot;Who's got the correct DPS?&quot;.  It's quite possible that mobs might not be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> that</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> much tougher...just (and I cringe as I type this) <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> smarter</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
The second thing, and this I find disappointing, is that some might even let the whole pet thing go.  What, pray tell, is our class design then?   Still damage?  Without our pets, we have only damage shields and our nukes.  Given that we have to camp the Creator to keep our DS title and at least 1 maybe 2 classes arguably can out nuke us now <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> besides</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> wizards (who should be able to, how else are we going to do damage?  Summoned weapons with insane procs?  Ah....Vending machine, thanks, I'll play something else now.  Summoned mod rod 3?  Drop it on the ground and mobs pick it up and are compelled to transverge to death?  No thanks again.<br>
<br>
Or ... are we supposed to undergo a complete transformation in our class design, greater than we already do?  I can't tell you how irate that would make me.<br>
<br>
I would be impressed if Verant showed some creativity...further, I really doubt Epic 2 will be a pet, at least, since the &quot;Old Guard&quot; has gone on record as saying they regretted it making it into the game (all those &quot;Mage Epic is too powerful&quot; comments by Verant before caster balancing started).  But that admittedly, is just speculation on my part.  I'd really be impressed if we got a series of buffs, instead...but, I'm not a game designer, so I won't go into specifics...as a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> gamer</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> though, and a devoted <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mage</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of some 1 and a half years, I don't like the notion of new pets...And that's not some petty psychological or emotional attachment to the Epic...it comes from a class balance and content perspective.<br>
<br>
